  "bib_entries": {
    "77149858": {
      "title": "Recognition of drainage fluid color of continuous bladder irrigation for doctors and nurses of urological department",
      "abstract": "Objective To understad the recognition of drainage fluid color of continuous bladder irrigation among medical staff. Methods A self-designed colorchecker and questionnaire were applied to 60 medical staff in 4 urological departments for the recognition of drainage fluid color. Results Except Color No. 5 (erythrocyte concentration at 2%) viewed unanimously as bright red,other colors had 2～4 recognition results with great significant chromatic aberration. All the medical staff selected different fluid color on irrigation speed adjustment,50% of them were unable to evaluate the blood volume based on the fluid color,50% varying significantly in the blood volume evaluation. Conclusion The recognition of drainage fluid color of continuous bladder irrigation is not based on any objective standards but on subjective cognition,which fails to correctly regulate the irrigation speed. Therefore,colorimetric card should be established,and standard for color recognition recording styles for bladder drop irrigation and drainage should be specified."
    }
